    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"embracing the moment\" feels like such a lie. it's just a way to distract ourselves from the fact that we're basically irrelevant. like, if you knew a movie was going to end in total silence and darkness forever, why would you even sit through it? it just feels like a waste of time to keep struggling when the outcome is already decided. everything is just a slow march toward nothingness.",
